## Steps to Reproduce

1. Make a flutter app that throws an exception. Any exception is good, such as `(null as bool?)!.toString();`.
2. Look at the logs. They are truncated, even though the "Include all stacktrace" option is enabled.

Example output log:
```
======== Exception caught by widgets library =======================================================
The following _TypeError was thrown building StreamBuilder<ToiletsState>(dirty, state: _StreamBuilderBaseState<ToiletsState, AsyncSnapshot<ToiletsState>>#67f51):
type 'Null' is not a subtype of type 'int' of 'function result'

The relevant error-causing widget was: 
  StoreConnector<AppState, UserState> file:///D:/dev/app/v1/lib/pages/my_page.dart:233:23
When the exception was thrown, this was the stack: 
#0      MyData.overallRatingSum (package:myapp/models/my_page.dart)
#1      MyDataSum.calcAggregatedScoreInformation.<anonymous closure> (package:myapp/pages/my_page.dart:62:23)
#2      List.forEach (dart:core-patch/growable_array.dart:403:8)
#3      v.calcAggregatedScoreInformation (package:myapp/pages/my_page.dart:60:13)
#4      _MyPageState._createDataForUser (package:myapp/pages/my_page.dart:205:41)
...
====================================================================================================
```

comment_data.body: @matanshukry Could you show us what the stack trace looks like when run from the command line?

Without additional information we're unfortunately not sure how to resolve this issue. We're going to close this bug for now, but please don't hesitate to comment on the bug if you have any more information for us; we're happy to reopen. Thanks for your contribution!
